<TITLE> Indonesia election exit poll puts Yudhoyono ahead: TV </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 JAKARTA, Wed Jul 8, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Indonesian President Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono is leading in the election with 51.07 percent of the vote, an exit poll issued by Metro Television showed on Wednesday. The exit poll is in line with indications in most opinion polls conducted ahead of the vote which had given Yudhoyono a clear lead. Yudhoyono is being challenged by Vice President Yusuf Kalla and former president Megawati Sukarnoputri, who had 15.2 percent and 19.21 percent, respectively, the exit poll showed. Metro television did not say how many people it had surveyed in the exit poll. Quick count surveys based on early counting are also expected to be released in the next few hours. Voting has ended in the east of the archipelago, but is still going on in much of Indonesia and is due to end at 0500 GMT. If no single candidate wins more than 50 percent of the vote, or 20 percent of the vote in 17 provinces, there will be a run-off between two candidates on Septemb
